#X text 819 708 The [adsr.m~] object is the MERDA version of [adsr~]. Check its help file., f 41;
#X msg 83 208 retrigger;
#X text 25 61 The [adsr~] object from ELSE is dedicated to ADSR envelopes. Check carefully the help file of [adsr~] as it's are quite high level and complex object. It works with a gate input or impulses. You can retrigger the envelope with the 'retrigger' message or an impulse in the 2nd inlet. Re-sending velocity values also retrigger it \, check the [pd mono/mono~] abstraction below., f 68;
#N canvas 165 181 685 569 mono 0;
#X obj 99 118 keyboard 17 80 4 2 1 0 empty empty;
#X obj 93 369 *~;
#X obj 208 379 vsl 18 100 0 1 0 0 ewtwet wefwert empty 0 -9 0 10 #dcdcdc #000000 #000000 0 1;
#X text 231 469 0;
#X text 231 375 1;
#X obj 93 413 out~;
#X obj 208 351 s2f~;
#X obj 111 313 adsr~ 100 100 0.5 250;
#X obj 99 260 mono;
#X obj 49 313 bl.saw~ -midi, f 7;
#X obj 328 369 *~;
#X obj 443 379 vsl 18 100 0 1 0 0 ewtwet wefwert empty 0 -9 0 10 #dcdcdc #000000 #000000 0 1;
#X text 466 467 0;
#X text 466 373 1;
