#X obj 284 313 bl.saw~ -midi, f 7;
#X obj 330 260 mono~;
#X text 125 34 Below we have both [mono] and [mono~] retriggering the envelope. The [keyboard] GUI has the toggle mode on so you can use is as a monophonic synth by clicking on other notes while one is pressed. Do it so you can retrigger it.;
#X text 411 219 The [mono~] object has an impulse output for retriggering. The [mono] object also has a bang outlet but it is not needed for [adsr~]. Check their help files., f 35;
#X connect 0 0 8 0;
#X connect 0 0 18 0;
#X connect 1 0 5 0;
#X connect 6 0 2 0;
#X connect 7 0 1 1;
#X connect 7 0 6 0;
#X connect 8 0 9 0;
#X connect 8 1 7 0;
#X connect 9 0 1 0;
#X connect 10 0 14 0;
#X connect 15 0 11 0;
#X connect 16 0 10 1;
#X connect 16 0 15 0;
#X connect 17 0 10 0;
#X connect 18 0 17 0;
#X connect 18 1 16 0;
#X connect 18 2 16 1;
#X restore 389 295 pd mono \; mono~;
#X text 14 407 You can also use the 'minsus' message or flag to trigger it with bangs or impulses for a "one shot" example. Below to the left \, it takes 500 ms before going into the release stage. By default you have a curvature of "1". We also have a "linear" mode (which is the same as setting the curve factor to 0). You can also combine to the maximum sustain parameter and have it also triggered by a gate. Below to the right it'll go into the release stage after 500ms regardless of the gate off status. Check the help file for more details., f 73;
#X text 549 31 We've seen other simpler envelope examples and all of them were possible with [adsr~] if you ignore one or more stages. Hence \, so you can just rely on it if you will. Let's review it. Below \, we have single decay envelope that can be triggered with a gate or impulse to the left. To the right we have an attack/release envelope \, or attack/decay \, where we just set the attack and decay phases with a minimum sustain of 0 and it'll work with either impulses or gates., f 72;
#X text 588 423 For last \, here's an envelope for attack/sustain/release \, where we ignore the decay stage and set the sustain point to '1'., f 32;
